static int rc522_read_regs(rc522_typdef *dev, unsigned char reg, unsigned char *dat, unsigned char len)
{
    int ret = -1;
    unsigned char txdata[len];
    unsigned char * rxdata;
    struct spi_message m;
    struct spi_transfer *t;
    struct spi_device *spi = dev->spi;
    
    t = kzalloc(sizeof(struct spi_transfer), GFP_KERNEL);   /* Áî≥ËØ∑ÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
    if(!t) {
        return -ENOMEM;
    }
    rxdata = kzalloc((sizeof(char) * len), GFP_KERNEL); /* Áî≥ËØ∑ÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
    if(!rxdata) {
        goto out1;
    }
    spi_cs_enable();
    /* ‰∏ÄÂÖ±ÂèëÈÄÅlen+1‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ，Á¨¨‰∏Ä‰∏™Â≠óËäÇ‰∏∫
    ÂØÑÂ≠òÂô®È¶ñÂú∞ÂùÄ，‰∏ÄÂÖ±Ë¶ÅËØªÂèñlen‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÈïøÂ∫¶ÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ，*/
    txdata[0] = ((reg << 1) & 0x7e) | 0x80;             
    t->tx_buf = txdata;         /* Ë¶ÅÂèëÈÄÅÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ */
    t->rx_buf = rxdata;         /* Ë¶ÅËØªÂèñÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ */
    t->len = len + 1;           /* t->len=ÂèëÈÄÅÁöÑÈïøÂ∫¶+ËØªÂèñÁöÑÈïøÂ∫¶ */
    spi_message_init(&m);       /* ÂàùÂßãÂåñspi_message */
    spi_message_add_tail(t, &m);/* Â∞Üspi_transferÊ∑ªÂä†Âà∞spi_messageÈòüÂàó */
    ret = spi_sync(spi, &m);    /* ÂêåÊ≠•ÂèëÈÄÅ */
    if(ret) {
        goto out2;
    }
    /* Âè™ÈúÄË¶ÅËØªÂèñÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ */
    memcpy(dat , rxdata + 1, len); /* Âè™ÈúÄË¶ÅËØªÂèñÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ */
out2:
    kfree(rxdata);                  /* ÈáäÊîæÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
out1:   
    kfree(t);                       /* ÈáäÊîæÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
    spi_cs_disable();
    return ret;
}
static int rc522_write_regs(rc522_typdef *dev, unsigned char reg, unsigned char *dat, unsigned char len)
{
    int ret = -1;
    unsigned char *txdata;
    struct spi_message m;
    struct spi_transfer *t;
    struct spi_device *spi = dev->spi;
    
    t = kzalloc(sizeof(struct spi_transfer), GFP_KERNEL);   /* Áî≥ËØ∑ÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
    if(!t) {
        return -ENOMEM;
    }
    
    txdata = kzalloc(sizeof(char) + len, GFP_KERNEL);
    if(!txdata) {
        goto out1;
    }
    spi_cs_enable();
    /* ‰∏ÄÂÖ±ÂèëÈÄÅlen+1‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ，Á¨¨‰∏Ä‰∏™Â≠óËäÇ‰∏∫
    ÂØÑÂ≠òÂô®È¶ñÂú∞ÂùÄ，len‰∏∫Ë¶ÅÂÜôÂÖ•ÁöÑÂØÑÂ≠òÂô®ÁöÑÈõÜÂêà，*/
    *txdata = ((reg << 1) & 0x7e);  /* ÂÜôÊï∞ÊçÆÁöÑÊó∂ÂÄôÈ¶ñÂØÑÂ≠òÂô®Âú∞ÂùÄbit8Ë¶ÅÊ∏ÖÈõ∂ */
    memcpy(txdata + 1, dat, len);
    t->tx_buf = txdata;         /* Ë¶ÅÂèëÈÄÅÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆ */
    t->len = len + 1;                   /* t->len=ÂèëÈÄÅÁöÑÈïøÂ∫¶+ËØªÂèñÁöÑÈïøÂ∫¶ */
    spi_message_init(&m);       /* ÂàùÂßãÂåñspi_message */
    spi_message_add_tail(t, &m);/* Â∞Üspi_transferÊ∑ªÂä†Âà∞spi_messageÈòüÂàó */
    ret = spi_sync(spi, &m);    /* ÂêåÊ≠•ÂèëÈÄÅ */
    if(ret) {
        goto out2;
    }
    
out2:
    kfree(txdata);      /* ÈáäÊîæÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
out1:
    kfree(t);                   /* ÈáäÊîæÂÜÖÂ≠ò */
    spi_cs_disable();
    return ret; 
}
static unsigned char read_one_reg(rc522_typdef *dev, unsigned char reg)
{
    unsigned char data = 0;
    rc522_read_regs(dev, reg, &data, 1);
    return data;    
}
static void write_one_reg(rc522_typdef *dev,unsigned char reg, unsigned char value)
{
    rc522_write_regs(dev, reg, &value, 1);
}
static int rc522_open(struct inode *inode, struct file *filp)
{
    filp->private_data = &rc522_dev;
   
    spi_rst_disable();
    udelay(10);
    spi_rst_enable();
    udelay(10);
    spi_rst_disable();
    printk("rc522_open ok!\n");
    return 0;
}
static int rc522_release(struct inode* inode ,struct file *filp)
{
    spi_rst_enable();
    gpio_free(rc522_dev.rstpin);
    printk("rc522_release ok!\n");   
    return 0;
}

static ssize_t  rc522_write(struct file *filp, const char __user *buf,size_t count, loff_t *f_pos)
{
    unsigned char *write_buf;/*Êï∞ÊçÆÁºìÂÜ≤Âå∫*/
    int ret;
    write_buf = (unsigned char*)kzalloc(count, GFP_KERNEL);
    if(!write_buf )
       return -ENOMEM;
    ret = copy_from_user(write_buf, buf, count);
    if (ret < 0)
    {
        kfree(write_buf);
        printk("copy from user failed!\r\n");
        return ret;
    }
    write_one_reg(&rc522_dev, write_buf[0], write_buf[1]);
    return 0;
}
static ssize_t rc522_read(struct file *filp,char __user *buf, size_t count,loff_t *f_pos)
{
    int ret; 
    unsigned char adr,value; 
    ret = copy_from_user(&adr, buf, 1);
    if(ret < 0)
    {
        printk("copy from user failed!\r\n");
        return ret;
    }
    value = read_one_reg(&rc522_dev, adr);
    ret = copy_to_user(buf, &value, count);
    if (ret < 0)
    {
        printk("copy to user failed!\r\n");
        return ret;
    }
    return ret;
}
static struct file_operations rc522_fops={
    .owner      = THIS_MODULE,
    .open       = rc522_open,
    .write      = rc522_write,
    .read       = rc522_read,
    .release    = rc522_release,
    // .llseek     = rc522_llseek,
};
        
static int rc522_probe(struct spi_device *spi)
{
    int ret;
    const char *string = NULL;
    
    printk("rc522 probe!\n"); 
   /*Ëé∑ÂèñËÆæÂ§áËäÇÁÇπ*/
   rc522_dev.node = of_find_node_by_path("/spi@fe610000/rc522@0");
   if(rc522_dev.node == NULL)
   {
      printk("device-tree:not found rc522!\r\n"); 
      return -1;
   }
   /*ËØªÂèñrc522ËÆæÂ§áËäÇÁÇπÁöÑcompatibleÂ±ûÊÄßÂÄº*/
   ret = of_property_read_string(rc522_dev.node, "compatible", &string);
   if(ret == 0)
   {
       printk("%s\n",string);
   }   
   rc522_dev.rstpin = of_get_named_gpio(rc522_dev.node,"rst-gpio",0);
   if(!gpio_is_valid(rc522_dev.rstpin))
   {
        printk("get gpio error\n");
        ret = -EINVAL;
        return ret;
   }
   
   printk("gpio = %d\n",rc522_dev.rstpin);
   ret = gpio_request(rc522_dev.rstpin,"spi-rst");
   if(ret < 0) 
   {
      printk("gpio_request %d failed\n", rc522_dev.rstpin);
      return ret;
   }
   gpio_direction_output(rc522_dev.rstpin, 1);
   gpio_export(rc522_dev.rstpin, 1);
    /*Áî≥ËØ∑ËÆæÂ§áÂè∑*/
    ret = alloc_chrdev_region(&rc522_dev.dev_id, 0, 1, DEVICE_NAME);
    if(ret < 0)
    {
         printk("alloc dev_id error %d\n", ret);
         return ret;
    }
   /*ÂàùÂßãÂåñ‰∏Ä‰∏™cdev*/
   cdev_init(&rc522_dev.cdev, &rc522_fops);
   /*Âêëcdev‰∏≠Ê∑ªÂä†‰∏Ä‰∏™ËÆæÂ§á*/
   ret = cdev_add(&rc522_dev.cdev, rc522_dev.dev_id, 1);
   if(ret != 0)
   {
        printk("cdev add error %d \n",ret);
        // goto Error;
   }
   /*ÂàõÂª∫‰∏Ä‰∏™nfc_classÁ±ª*/
   rc522_dev.class = class_create(THIS_MODULE, "nfc_class");
   if(rc522_dev.class == NULL)
   {
      printk("class_create failed\r\n");
      return -1;
   }
   /*Âú®nfc_classÁ±ª‰∏ãÂàõÂª∫‰∏Ä‰∏™NFC_classËÆæÂ§á*/
   rc522_dev.device = device_create(rc522_dev.class, NULL, rc522_dev.dev_id, NULL, DEVICE_NAME);   
   /*Ëé∑Âèñ‰∏éÊú¨È©±Âä®ÂåπÈÖçÁöÑspiËÆæÂ§á*/
   rc522_dev.spi = spi;
   spi_setup(rc522_dev.spi);   
   
    return 0;
}
static int rc522_remove(struct spi_device *spi)
{
    printk("w25qxx remove!\n"); 
    /*Âà†Èô§rc522Á±ª*/
    cdev_del(&rc522_dev.cdev);
    /*ÈáäÊîærc522ËÆæÂ§áÂè∑*/
    unregister_chrdev_region(rc522_dev.dev_id, 1);
    /*Ê≥®ÈîÄrc522ËÆæÂ§á*/
    device_destroy(rc522_dev.class, rc522_dev.dev_id);
    /*Ê≥®ÈîÄrc522Á±ª*/
    class_destroy(rc522_dev.class);
    gpio_free(rc522_dev.rstpin);
    return 0;   
}
static const struct of_device_id rc522_of_match[] = {
   {.compatible = "topeet,rc522"},
   {},
};
static const struct spi_device_id rc522_id[] = {
    { "xxxx", 0 },
    {},
};
static struct spi_driver rc522_driver = {
    .driver = {
        .owner = THIS_MODULE,       
        .name =  "rc522",
        .of_match_table = rc522_of_match,
    },
    .probe = rc522_probe,
    .remove = rc522_remove,
    .id_table = rc522_id,
};
static int __init rc522_init(void)
{
   int ret;
   ret = spi_register_driver(&rc522_driver);
   if(ret < 0)
   {
        printk("spi_register_driver error= %d \n",ret);
   }
   else
   {
        printk("module init ok\n");
   }
   return ret;
}
static void rc522_exit(void)
{
    spi_unregister_driver(&rc522_driver);  
    printk("module exit ok\n");
}
module_init(rc522_init);
module_exit(rc522_exit);
MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");

unsigned char ReadRawRC(unsigned char Address)
{
  unsigned char buf[1]; 
  buf[0] = Address;
   read(fd,buf,1);  
  return buf[0];  
}
void WriteRawRC(unsigned char Address, unsigned char Value)
{  
  unsigned char buf[2];
  buf[0] = Address;
  buf[1] = Value;
  write(fd,buf,2);  
}
void SetBitMask(unsigned char ucReg, unsigned char ucMask)  
{
  unsigned char ucTemp;
  ucTemp = ReadRawRC ( ucReg );
  WriteRawRC (ucReg, ucTemp | ucMask); // set bit mask
}
void ClearBitMask(unsigned char ucReg, unsigned char ucMask)  
{
  unsigned char ucTemp;
  ucTemp = ReadRawRC (ucReg);
  WriteRawRC (ucReg, ucTemp & ( ~ ucMask)); // clear bit mask
}
void PcdAntennaOn(void)
{
  unsigned char uc;
  uc = ReadRawRC (TxControlReg);
  if (! ( uc & 0x03 ))
  {
      SetBitMask(TxControlReg, 0x03);   
  }
}
static void PcdAntennaOff(void)
{
    ClearBitMask(TxControlReg, 0x03);
}
int PcdReset(void)
{
  fd = open("/dev/nfc", O_RDWR);
    if(fd < 0)
    {
        printf("open rc522_drv error %d\n",fd);
      return fd;
  }
  WriteRawRC ( CommandReg, 0x0f );
  
  while ( ReadRawRC ( CommandReg ) & 0x10 );
 
   //ÂÆö‰πâÂèëÈÄÅÂíåÊé•Êî∂Â∏∏Áî®Ê®°Âºè ÂíåMifareÂç°ÈÄöËÆØ，CRCÂàùÂßãÂÄº0x6363
   WriteRawRC ( ModeReg, 0x3D );          
   WriteRawRC ( TReloadRegL, 30 );      //16‰ΩçÂÆöÊó∂Âô®‰Ωé‰Ωç   
   WriteRawRC ( TReloadRegH, 0 );      //16‰ΩçÂÆöÊó∂Âô®È´ò‰Ωç 
   WriteRawRC ( TModeReg, 0x8D );      //ÂÆö‰πâÂÜÖÈÉ®ÂÆöÊó∂Âô®ÁöÑËÆæÁΩÆ 
   WriteRawRC ( TPrescalerReg, 0x3E );   //ËÆæÁΩÆÂÆöÊó∂Âô®ÂàÜÈ¢ëÁ≥ªÊï∞  
   WriteRawRC ( TxAutoReg, 0x40 );       //Ë∞ÉÂà∂ÂèëÈÄÅ‰ø°Âè∑‰∏∫100%ASK 
  return 1;
}
char M500PcdConfigISOType ( unsigned char ucType )
{
  if ( ucType == 'A')                     //ISO14443_A
   {
      ClearBitMask ( Status2Reg, 0x08 );    
      WriteRawRC ( ModeReg, 0x3D );         //3F    
      WriteRawRC ( RxSelReg, 0x86 );        //84    
      WriteRawRC( RFCfgReg, 0x7F );         //4F    
      WriteRawRC( TReloadRegL, 30 );            
      WriteRawRC ( TReloadRegH, 0 );    
      WriteRawRC ( TModeReg, 0x8D );    
      WriteRawRC ( TPrescalerReg, 0x3E );   
      usleep(10000);    
      PcdAntennaOn ();//ÂºÄÂ§©Á∫ø   
   } 
   else
   {
      return MI_ERR;
   }
   return MI_OK;   
}
char PcdComMF522 ( unsigned char ucCommand, unsigned char * pInData, unsigned char ucInLenByte, unsigned char * pOutData,unsigned int * pOutLenBit )    
{
  char cStatus = MI_ERR;
  unsigned char ucIrqEn   = 0x00;
  unsigned char ucWaitFor = 0x00;
  unsigned char ucLastBits;
  unsigned char ucN;
  unsigned int ul;
  switch ( ucCommand )
  {
     case PCD_AUTHENT:      //MifareËÆ§ËØÅ
        ucIrqEn   = 0x12;   //ÂÖÅËÆ∏ÈîôËØØ‰∏≠Êñ≠ËØ∑Ê±ÇErrIEn  ÂÖÅËÆ∏Á©∫Èó≤‰∏≠Êñ≠IdleIEn
        ucWaitFor = 0x10;   //ËÆ§ËØÅÂØªÂç°Á≠âÂæÖÊó∂ÂÄô Êü•ËØ¢Á©∫Èó≤‰∏≠Êñ≠Ê†áÂøó‰Ωç
        break;
     
     case PCD_TRANSCEIVE:   //Êé•Êî∂ÂèëÈÄÅ ÂèëÈÄÅÊé•Êî∂
        ucIrqEn   = 0x77;   //ÂÖÅËÆ∏TxIEn RxIEn IdleIEn LoAlertIEn ErrIEn TimerIEn
        ucWaitFor = 0x30;   //ÂØªÂç°Á≠âÂæÖÊó∂ÂÄô Êü•ËØ¢Êé•Êî∂‰∏≠Êñ≠Ê†áÂøó‰Ωç‰∏é Á©∫Èó≤‰∏≠Êñ≠Ê†áÂøó‰Ωç
        break;
     
     default:
       break;     
  }
  //IRqInvÁΩÆ‰ΩçÁÆ°ËÑöIRQ‰∏éStatus1RegÁöÑIRq‰ΩçÁöÑÂÄºÁõ∏Âèç 
  WriteRawRC ( ComIEnReg, ucIrqEn | 0x80 );
  //Set1ËØ•‰ΩçÊ∏ÖÈõ∂Êó∂，CommIRqRegÁöÑÂ±èËîΩ‰ΩçÊ∏ÖÈõ∂
  ClearBitMask ( ComIrqReg, 0x80 );  
  //ÂÜôÁ©∫Èó≤ÂëΩ‰ª§
  WriteRawRC ( CommandReg, PCD_IDLE );     
  
  //ÁΩÆ‰ΩçFlushBufferÊ∏ÖÈô§ÂÜÖÈÉ®FIFOÁöÑËØªÂíåÂÜôÊåáÈíà‰ª•ÂèäErrRegÁöÑBufferOvflÊ†áÂøó‰ΩçË¢´Ê∏ÖÈô§
  SetBitMask ( FIFOLevelReg, 0x80 );      
  for ( ul = 0; ul < ucInLenByte; ul ++ )
  {
      WriteRawRC ( FIFODataReg, pInData [ ul ] ); //ÂÜôÊï∞ÊçÆËøõFIFOdata
  }
    
  WriteRawRC ( CommandReg, ucCommand );         //ÂÜôÂëΩ‰ª§
  if ( ucCommand == PCD_TRANSCEIVE )
  {  
      //StartSendÁΩÆ‰ΩçÂêØÂä®Êï∞ÊçÆÂèëÈÄÅ ËØ•‰Ωç‰∏éÊî∂ÂèëÂëΩ‰ª§‰ΩøÁî®Êó∂ÊâçÊúâÊïà
      SetBitMask(BitFramingReg,0x80);           
  }
  ul = 1000;                             //Ê†πÊçÆÊó∂ÈíüÈ¢ëÁéáË∞ÉÊï¥，Êìç‰ΩúM1Âç°ÊúÄÂ§ßÁ≠âÂæÖÊó∂Èó¥25ms
  do                                     //ËÆ§ËØÅ ‰∏éÂØªÂç°Á≠âÂæÖÊó∂Èó¥ 
  {
       ucN = ReadRawRC ( ComIrqReg );    //Êü•ËØ¢‰∫ã‰ª∂‰∏≠Êñ≠
       ul --;
  } while ( ( ul != 0 ) && ( ! ( ucN & 0x01 ) ) && ( ! ( ucN & ucWaitFor ) ) ); 
  ClearBitMask ( BitFramingReg, 0x80 );  //Ê∏ÖÁêÜÂÖÅËÆ∏StartSend‰Ωç
  if ( ul != 0 )
  {
    //ËØªÈîôËØØÊ†áÂøóÂØÑÂ≠òÂô®BufferOfI CollErr ParityErr ProtocolErr
    if ( ! ( ReadRawRC ( ErrorReg ) & 0x1B ) )  
    {
      cStatus = MI_OK;
      
      if ( ucN & ucIrqEn & 0x01 )       //ÊòØÂê¶ÂèëÁîüÂÆöÊó∂Âô®‰∏≠Êñ≠
        cStatus = MI_NOTAGERR;   
        
      if ( ucCommand == PCD_TRANSCEIVE )
      {
        //ËØªFIFO‰∏≠‰øùÂ≠òÁöÑÂ≠óËäÇÊï∞
        ucN = ReadRawRC ( FIFOLevelReg );             
        
        //ÊúÄÂêéÊé•Êî∂Âà∞ÂæóÂ≠óËäÇÁöÑÊúâÊïà‰ΩçÊï∞
        ucLastBits = ReadRawRC ( ControlReg ) & 0x07; 
        
        if ( ucLastBits )
          
          //N‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÊï∞ÂáèÂéª1（ÊúÄÂêé‰∏Ä‰∏™Â≠óËäÇ）+ÊúÄÂêé‰∏Ä‰ΩçÁöÑ‰ΩçÊï∞ ËØªÂèñÂà∞ÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆÊÄª‰ΩçÊï∞
          * pOutLenBit = ( ucN - 1 ) * 8 + ucLastBits;    
        else
          * pOutLenBit = ucN * 8;      //ÊúÄÂêéÊé•Êî∂Âà∞ÁöÑÂ≠óËäÇÊï¥‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÊúâÊïà
        
        if ( ucN == 0 )   
          ucN = 1;    
        
        if ( ucN > MAXRLEN )
          ucN = MAXRLEN;   
        
        for ( ul = 0; ul < ucN; ul ++ )
          pOutData [ ul ] = ReadRawRC ( FIFODataReg );   
        
        }        
    }   
    else
      cStatus = MI_ERR;       
  }
  SetBitMask ( ControlReg, 0x80 );           // stop timer now
  WriteRawRC ( CommandReg, PCD_IDLE ); 
   
  return cStatus;
}
char PcdRequest (unsigned char ucReq_code, unsigned char * pTagType)
{
  char cStatus;  
  unsigned char ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ]; 
  unsigned int ulLen;
  //Ê∏ÖÁêÜÊåáÁ§∫MIFARECyptolÂçïÂÖÉÊé•ÈÄö‰ª•ÂèäÊâÄÊúâÂç°ÁöÑÊï∞ÊçÆÈÄö‰ø°Ë¢´Âä†ÂØÜÁöÑÊÉÖÂÜµ
  ClearBitMask ( Status2Reg, 0x08 );
  //ÂèëÈÄÅÁöÑÊúÄÂêé‰∏Ä‰∏™Â≠óËäÇÁöÑ ‰∏É‰Ωç
  WriteRawRC ( BitFramingReg, 0x07 );
  //ClearBitMask ( TxControlReg, 0x03 );  
  //TX1,TX2ÁÆ°ËÑöÁöÑËæìÂá∫‰ø°Âè∑‰º†ÈÄíÁªèÂèëÈÄÅË∞ÉÂà∂ÁöÑ13.56ÁöÑËÉΩÈáèËΩΩÊ≥¢‰ø°Âè∑
  //usleep(10000); 
  SetBitMask ( TxControlReg, 0x03 );  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = ucReq_code;   //Â≠òÂÖ• Âç°ÁâáÂëΩ‰ª§Â≠ó
  cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE, ucComMF522Buf, 1, ucComMF522Buf,& ulLen );  //ÂØªÂç°  
  if ( ( cStatus == MI_OK ) && ( ulLen == 0x10 ) )  //ÂØªÂç°ÊàêÂäüËøîÂõûÂç°Á±ªÂûã 
  {    
     * pTagType = ucComMF522Buf[0];
     * ( pTagType + 1 ) = ucComMF522Buf[1];
  }
  else
  {
      cStatus = MI_ERR;
  }
  return cStatus;  
}
char PcdAnticoll ( unsigned char * pSnr )
{
  char cStatus;
  unsigned char uc, ucSnr_check = 0;
  unsigned char ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ]; 
  unsigned int ulLen;
  
  //Ê∏ÖMFCryptol On‰Ωç Âè™ÊúâÊàêÂäüÊâßË°åMFAuthentÂëΩ‰ª§Âêé，ËØ•‰ΩçÊâçËÉΩÁΩÆ‰Ωç
  ClearBitMask ( Status2Reg, 0x08 );
  //Ê∏ÖÁêÜÂØÑÂ≠òÂô® ÂÅúÊ≠¢Êî∂Âèë
  WriteRawRC ( BitFramingReg, 0x00);  
  //Ê∏ÖValuesAfterCollÊâÄÊúâÊé•Êî∂ÁöÑ‰ΩçÂú®ÂÜ≤Á™ÅÂêéË¢´Ê∏ÖÈô§
  ClearBitMask ( CollReg, 0x80 );       
 
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = 0x93;           //Âç°ÁâáÈò≤ÂÜ≤Á™ÅÂëΩ‰ª§
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = 0x20;
 
  cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE, 
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          2, 
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          & ulLen);      //‰∏éÂç°ÁâáÈÄö‰ø°
  if ( cStatus == MI_OK)                //ÈÄö‰ø°ÊàêÂäü
  {
    for ( uc = 0; uc < 4; uc ++ )
    {
       * ( pSnr + uc )  = ucComMF522Buf [ uc ]; //ËØªÂá∫UID
       ucSnr_check ^= ucComMF522Buf [ uc ];
    }
    
    if ( ucSnr_check != ucComMF522Buf [ uc ] )
      cStatus = MI_ERR;            
  }
  
  SetBitMask ( CollReg, 0x80 );
      
  return cStatus;   
}
void CalulateCRC ( unsigned char * pIndata, unsigned char ucLen, unsigned char * pOutData )
{
  unsigned char uc, ucN;
  ClearBitMask(DivIrqReg,0x04);
  WriteRawRC(CommandReg,PCD_IDLE);
  SetBitMask(FIFOLevelReg,0x80);
  for ( uc = 0; uc < ucLen; uc ++)
    WriteRawRC ( FIFODataReg, * ( pIndata + uc ) );   
  WriteRawRC ( CommandReg, PCD_CALCCRC );
  uc = 0xFF;
  do 
  {
      ucN = ReadRawRC ( DivIrqReg );
      uc --;
  } while ( ( uc != 0 ) && ! ( ucN & 0x04 ) );
  
  pOutData [ 0 ] = ReadRawRC ( CRCResultRegL );
  pOutData [ 1 ] = ReadRawRC ( CRCResultRegM );   
}
char PcdSelect ( unsigned char * pSnr )
{
  char ucN;
  unsigned char uc;
  unsigned char ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ]; 
  unsigned int  ulLen;
  
  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = PICC_ANTICOLL1;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = 0x70;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 6 ] = 0;
  for ( uc = 0; uc < 4; uc ++ )
  {
    ucComMF522Buf [ uc + 2 ] = * ( pSnr + uc );
    ucComMF522Buf [ 6 ] ^= * ( pSnr + uc );
  }
  
  CalulateCRC ( ucComMF522Buf, 7, & ucComMF522Buf [ 7 ] );
  ClearBitMask ( Status2Reg, 0x08 );
  ucN = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE,
                     ucComMF522Buf,
                     9,
                     ucComMF522Buf, 
                     & ulLen );
  
  if ( ( ucN == MI_OK ) && ( ulLen == 0x18 ) )
    ucN = MI_OK;  
  else
    ucN = MI_ERR;    
  
  return ucN;   
}
char PcdAuthState ( unsigned char ucAuth_mode, unsigned char ucAddr, unsigned char * pKey, unsigned char * pSnr )
{
  char cStatus;
  unsigned char uc, ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ];
  unsigned int ulLen;
  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = ucAuth_mode;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = ucAddr;
  for ( uc = 0; uc < 6; uc ++ )
    ucComMF522Buf [ uc + 2 ] = * ( pKey + uc );   
  for ( uc = 0; uc < 6; uc ++ )
    ucComMF522Buf [ uc + 8 ] = * ( pSnr + uc );   
  cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_AUTHENT,
                          ucComMF522Buf, 
                          12,
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          & ulLen );
  if ( ( cStatus != MI_OK ) || ( ! ( ReadRawRC ( Status2Reg ) & 0x08 ) ) )
    cStatus = MI_ERR;   
    
  return cStatus;
}
char PcdWrite ( unsigned char ucAddr, unsigned char * pData )
{
  char cStatus;
  unsigned char uc, ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ];
  unsigned int ulLen;
   
  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = PICC_WRITE;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = ucAddr;
  CalulateCRC ( ucComMF522Buf, 2, & ucComMF522Buf [ 2 ] );
  cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE,
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          4, 
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          & ulLen );
  if ( ( cStatus != MI_OK ) || ( ulLen != 4 ) || 
         ( ( ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] & 0x0F ) != 0x0A ) )
    cStatus = MI_ERR;   
      
  if ( cStatus == MI_OK )
  {
    //memcpy(ucComMF522Buf, pData, 16);
    for ( uc = 0; uc < 16; uc ++ )
      ucComMF522Buf [ uc ] = * ( pData + uc );  
    
    CalulateCRC ( ucComMF522Buf, 16, & ucComMF522Buf [ 16 ] );
    cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE,
                           ucComMF522Buf, 
                           18, 
                           ucComMF522Buf,
                           & ulLen );
    
    if ( ( cStatus != MI_OK ) || ( ulLen != 4 ) || 
         ( ( ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] & 0x0F ) != 0x0A ) )
      cStatus = MI_ERR;   
    
  }   
  return cStatus;   
}
char PcdRead ( unsigned char ucAddr, unsigned char * pData )
{
  char cStatus;
  unsigned char uc, ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ]; 
  unsigned int ulLen;
  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = PICC_READ;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = ucAddr;
  CalulateCRC ( ucComMF522Buf, 2, & ucComMF522Buf [ 2 ] );
 
  cStatus = PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE,
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          4, 
                          ucComMF522Buf,
                          & ulLen );
  if ( ( cStatus == MI_OK ) && ( ulLen == 0x90 ) )
  {
    for ( uc = 0; uc < 16; uc ++ )
      * ( pData + uc ) = ucComMF522Buf [ uc ];   
  }
  
  else
    cStatus = MI_ERR;   
   
  return cStatus;   
}
char PcdHalt( void )
{
  unsigned char ucComMF522Buf [ MAXRLEN ]; 
  unsigned int  ulLen;
  
  ucComMF522Buf [ 0 ] = PICC_HALT;
  ucComMF522Buf [ 1 ] = 0;
  
   CalulateCRC ( ucComMF522Buf, 2, & ucComMF522Buf [ 2 ] );
  PcdComMF522 ( PCD_TRANSCEIVE,
                ucComMF522Buf,
                4, 
                ucComMF522Buf, 
                & ulLen );
  return MI_OK; 
}
int main(int argc, const char * argv [ ])
{
   int ret = -1;
  unsigned char KeyValue[]={0xFF ,0xFF, 0xFF, 0xFF, 0xFF, 0xFF};   // Âç°AÂØÜÈí•
  char cStr [ 30 ], writebuf[16], readbuf[16];
  unsigned char ucArray_ID [ 4 ];    /*ÂÖàÂêéÂ≠òÊîæICÂç°ÁöÑÁ±ªÂûãÂíåUID(ICÂç°Â∫èÂàóÂè∑)*/                                                                                         
  unsigned char ucStatusReturn, snr;      /*ËøîÂõûÁä∂ÊÄÅ*/     
    
   snr = 1; //ÊâáÂå∫Âè∑
  ret = PcdReset();
  if(ret < 0)
  {
        printf("rc522 rst error %d \n",ret);
      return 0;
  }
  ucStatusReturn = M500PcdConfigISOType ( 'A' );
   if(ucStatusReturn == MI_ERR)
   {
      printf("M500PcdConfigISOType error! \n");
   }
   else
   {
      printf("M500PcdConfigISOType normal! \n");
   }
   while(1)
   {
         ucStatusReturn = PcdRequest ( PICC_REQIDL, ucArray_ID ); 
         if ( ucStatusReturn == MI_OK )  
         {
            if ( PcdAnticoll ( ucArray_ID ) == MI_OK )  
            {
                  PcdSelect(ucArray_ID);      // ÈÄâÂç° 
                  ucStatusReturn = PcdAuthState(KEYA, (snr*4 + 3) , KeyValue, ucArray_ID );//Ê†°È™åÂØÜÁ†Å 
                  if(ucStatusReturn !=  MI_OK)
                  {
                     sprintf(cStr, "The Card ID is: %02X%02X%02X%02X",ucArray_ID [0], ucArray_ID [1], ucArray_ID [2],ucArray_ID [3]);
                     printf("%s\r\n",cStr);  //ÊâìÂç∞Âç°ÁâáID 
                  }
                  else
                  {
                        printf("rc522 card number err!\r\n");
                  }
                  if(PcdWrite((snr*4 + 3) , writebuf) == MI_OK)
                  {
                     printf("PcdWrite Success! \r\n");
                  }
                  if(PcdRead((snr*4 + 3) , readbuf) == MI_OK)
                  {
                     print_data("read block", readbuf, 16);            
                  }
                  else
                  {
                     printf("PcdRead err! \r\n");
                  }
            } 
            else
            {
                  PcdHalt();
            }                                       
         }
   }
   return 0; 
}
